description:
Host your wedding with beautiful view and private access to Shediac Bay

name: Entire Private Island + 6 Bedroom House 2 Hot Tubs
description:
Indulge in the stay of a lifetime on your very own private island! Enjoy 9 acres of rugged nature and modern luxuries.

The Lakehouse: 6 bedrooms, 4,500+ sq. ft., for up to 12 guests. Breathtaking water views from every window, high-speed WiFi, 3-length boat dock, large front and back decks, private beaches, 5 TVs, fire pit, upgraded kitchen, bar, games room, whirlpool and soaker tubs, and two hot tubs facing sunrise and sunset.

Book now for the perfect blend of serenity and sophistication!
neighborhood_overview:
Local Attractions & Amenities:

Maquapit Lake: Renowned for its serene beauty, perfect for swimming, boating, and fishing.

Nearby Nature Reserves: Explore lush forests and scenic trails ideal for hiking, birdwatching, and wildlife spotting.

Historical Sites: Discover the rich history of New Brunswick with visits to local landmarks and museums.

Cultural Experiences: Enjoy local festivals, farmers' markets, and artisan shops showcasing the best of New Brunswick's culture and crafts.

Outdoor Adventures: Engage in thrilling activities like jet skiing, ice skating, cross-country skiing, and snowmobiling in the surrounding areas.

Away from it all! ...But nothing is out of reach:
Just 25 minutes from an international airport, 30 minutes from the nearest urban city center, and only 8 minutes to a convenience store, liquor store, and seasonal take-out restaurants.

neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Gatherings Guest House is on 1.25 acres, parking for 8 located on the beautiful Saint John River Valley just a few minutes from Fredericton, New Brunswick's capital. Being the capital of the province our city has no industrial manufacturing so our air is very fresh and clean for you to enjoy while you relax on your vacation while you stay with us.
Just a few Kilometres up river we have a Mactaquac provincial park that has an 18 hole golf course, provincial camping, a marina and a swimming.
There are three more golf courses in this are they are; Kingswood, Fredericton Golf club and they also have an indoor curling club and carman creek golf course.

We love to travel, entertain and have dinner parties and visit with friends and family in our wonderful River Home.  We have two lovely black Labradors and we all love to spend time in this beautiful space on the water!

name: Bay of Fundy Oceanfront Retreat
description: Imagine 1000 feet of your own private beach on the ever-changing Bay of Fundy.  Share this pristine waterfront with playful seals and migratory birds.  A true nature lover's paradise, yet only 20 minutes from  St. John, NB and an hour to the U.S.
neighborhood_overview: This private beach house is located between two fishing villages.  The city of St. John and the ferry to Nova Scotia are 20 minutes away.  There are abundant hiking and bicycle trails in the area.  Kayak rentals are 2 km from the house.  The U.S. border in Calais, Maine, is an hour's drive.  The Hopewell Rocks are less than 2 hours from the house.  Fredericton is 1 1/2 hours and Moncton 1 hour.
host_about: I am a single woman living between Maine, Connecticut, and Fiorida..  I run a seasonal bed and breakfast in my riverfront home in Calais, Maine.  I enjoy  travel and meeting people from all parts of the world and hosting a bed and breakfast has been a wonderful way to accomplish just that.

name: LongJohns Lodge-right on the trail!
description:
LongJohns Lodge -in the snowmobile capital of Atlantic Canada!
Only 3 mins from Nepisiguit Sports Lodge and direct access to miles of the best trails! Whether it be for snowmobiling, ATVing, hunting or fishing in the Nepisiguit River or just a nice hike, there is something for everyone. Relax by the fireplace with your family. Perfect for work or for an any season getaway. This spacious lodge has plenty of room to enjoy. 27 mins to Bathurst to visit beaches, golfing, dining, shopping...
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to LongJohns Lodge!
Nepisiguit Falls area is beautiful every season throughout the year! The Nepisiguit river flows right to the top of the falls where one of the oldest dams in New Brunswick produces electricity.
Great for all outdoor enthusiasts !
You can leave by ATV or sled right from the back door to access miles of the best trails!

In the summer the river offers crystal clear water which is great for swimming, fishing & boating of all kinds .
The spring & fall seasons are breathtaking!
The spring brings the thaw of the river- the waterfall is thunderous, powerful and amazing! A quick run in your ATV will get you to beautiful Papineau Falls as well.
The Fall season is breathtaking with its amazing colours of the fall foliage! Avid hunters love it here!
Wintertime is when the place really wakes up to fun in the snow! Located only 3 mins from Nepisiguit Sports Lodge, Snowmobile Club #1.
Not a sled head? No problem! Yo
host_about:
Hi there!
My name is Liana, my husband Doug and I are avid snowmobilers , ATVerâ€™s , boaters...well just about anything outside, we love!

Visitors can take advantage of the walking trails, two wooden boardwalks and the observation tower. Enjoy festivals and special events, the Farmersâ€™ Market, the outdoor beach theater and youth activities.

*Entire property can sleep 12 if you book both units-please inquire*

This is not your average Airbnb! This restored historical home is located in downtown Fredericton, in walking distance to shops, restaurants, The Playhouse, Convention Centre, and UNB.

It features 11 ft ceilings, gas fireplace, piano and modern amenities including kitchen with gas range and 2 dishwashers as well as 3 bdrms plus den with sofabed and 2.5 bathrooms with heated marble floors. Hottub, BBQ, gas fireplace outside!
host_about: I am a Realtor with eXp Realty. Orginally from Kincardine ON,   I live right downtown Fredericton NB with my husband, Joe, and my little dog, D.C.  Our Airbnb in Fredericton is attached to our own home, and our Airbnb in Kincardine is our Hometown Hideaway that we are thrilled to share with Airbnb guests while we aren't there, and is lovingly cared for by my mother and aunt.

name: Historic Edwardian Carriage House Ample Parking
description: The Gardeners Cottage in Saint Andrews New Brunswick is a place that's both historic and one of a kind.  Listed in the Canadian registry of historical places and designed by the prominent Maxwell Brothers Architects for the Ogilvie wheat baron F.W. Thompson. Part of the carriage house and stables building on the estate, the gardeners cottage was the home to the groomsmen and gardeners. In the shadow of the Algonquin Hotel close to Katy's Cove and walk-able to downtown Saint Andrews by the Sea.
neighborhood_overview: In the shadow of the mighty Algonquin Hotel The Gardeners Cottage is steps from the town tennis courts and a short walk to Katy's Cove! A very walk-able neighborhood with full time residents nearby. The popular Antique store Macklem House is very close, stop in to pick up a vintage souvenir. Historic Water Street is a quick jaunt down to the shore.  If you need your morning coffee fix Tim Hortons is just a couple of blocks away.

name: Cheerful Cottage, Short Walk owners PrivateBeach
description:
A lovely escape from the city for a large family or group getaway, in this peaceful fishing village on the Northumberland Strait, which boasts the warmest water in Atlantic Canada. Enjoy the fresh ocean air sipping your morning coffee on the deck.
Private beach is just 2 min drive or 10 minute walk.Plenty of nature to enjoy on the seaside trails, and forested walking and cycling trails. Enjoy fresh seafood, and local micro brewery , watching the sunset from the nearby waterfront restaurant.
neighborhood_overview:

description: Luxurious peaceful rustic wooden chalet surrounded by nature and wildlife on the edge of a tranquil natural pond next to a private sandy beach on the Atlantic ocean.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a picturesque postcard considered to be a beach community with many public provincial beaches, parks, sand dunes, forests, wildlife, parks, nature walking trails and boardwalks. In the area within 15 minutes of this location, you can also find a fish market, grocery store, gas station, boat marina, seafood restaurants and take-outs, bike rental, tourist office, leather shop, public library and there is also a 18 hole golf course 5 minutes away and a water park, casino, movie theatre,minature golf, zoo, butterfly sanctuary 30 minutes away. I would be happy to be your guide and advisor to the area, answering all your questons and giving you suggestions to maximize your experience during your stay.
host_about: The best way to describe my life is travel, adventure and being of service to others. The best way to describe myself is an eccentric world traveler, documentarian, humanitarian, alchemist, explorer who is in search for the truth and not a slave to the illusion of the system. I'm an open-minded and friendly guy who has been traveling the world for the past 26 years through 168 countries on 6 continents, from the roof of Africa on Mount Kilimanjaro in Tanzania, through the jungles of south-east Asia to the southern tip of Patagonia on Tierra del Fuego. This lifestyle has allowed me to share the love of many cultures, religions and races around the world. Always in motion to explore the splendors of our planet with a never-ending, ever-changing magnificent views and realities. I started my journey in 1988 and haven't looked back to the illusion. I am attracted to adventure, nature, cultural diversity, history, architecture, wildlife, anthropology and unique customs. My motivation for this choice of lifestyle is to experience, learn and meet as many people while witnessing as many traditional activities as I can during my life time. At the same time, my true passion is my humanitarian work supporting people in third world countries with education, water, food, medicine, business creation, life necessities and love. My main goal is to create a bridge from the developed world to the impoverished people of the world, creating equality and opportunity. Being a citizen of the world gives you the feeling of being connected to the entire planet and having a real understanding of the people who live on it makes you feel so appreciative to be alive and thankful to be apart of it. It makes you realize the whole world is our home and we are all family in it. This is why I am opening up my home to other travelers to stay while expanding my international network of friends. If you really want to know who I am and what I do, check out my documentaries on my Youtube channel at SELIM FEHMI OZCAN or my photos on my private website at True MyEyes. I hope our paths will cross someday somewhere in this world.

name: Campobello Island Cozy Cottage Retreats
description:
Vocational Summer Retreats & Cottage Living

Come Visit Une BelleVue Where Eagles Soar for:

â€¢ Personal Relaxation
â€¢ Weekend Getaways
â€¢ Intimate Getaways
â€¢ Romantic Getaways
â€¢ Pillow Talks
â€¢ Nature's Retreat
â€¢ Fresh Air Getaways

Our house, "Une BelleVue", is an 864 sq ft 2 bedroom cozy bungalow resting on an acre of spectacular views of the Atlantic Ocean, on the beautiful Island of Campobello, NB Canada. 15 minutes from Lubec, Maine.

Bookings Available For Quiet Time...
neighborhood_overview:
It's very peaceful here at "Une BelleVue", where the sunrise is a spectacular view from the house.

Most mornings you'll see the eagles and other birds flying over head calling to each other, enjoying the ocean breeze as they soar the skies. You will also see and hear our beautiful small squirrels scurrying around looking for food and woodpeckers pecking at the bark of the trees. Hope you get to see the "Pileated Woodpecker", they are big and beautiful.

If you bring your bikes there are lots of trails and parks to visit.

You can also drive around the Island, where you will have different views of nearby islands and see the ferry coming into Welshpool.

From the backyard or living room you will also see the Grand Manan Ferries in the distance as they sail by, and watch the fishing boats coming in or going out.

host_about:
Hiâ€¦.Iâ€™m Beth.  Iâ€™m a â€œmilitary bratâ€ who lived and travelled all over the world growing up.  Many of my summers were spent on the Mighty Miramichi, where my mom and generations before her were born.  I loved spending time with my Grandparents here, and have many fond memories of these New Brunswick summers. 
My Uncle and Aunt recently moved back to the Miramichi and ventured into the vacation rental business.  They opened up Cast Away Vacation rentals in May of 2020 and have thoroughly enjoyed helping guests create special and memorable vacations on the beautiful Miramichi River.
My husband Mike and I (with our three children) have decided to jump on board with the intent to carry on creating these exciting experiences for guests at the Lodge and at our newest property the Grand Lodge. 
We are pleased and proud to be assuming the reins of Cast Away Vacation Rentals in September of 2022.  We look forward to hosting you, your family and friends very soon!!!
~Beth and Mike

name: STOKE Luxury Cabin No. 1 With Epic Mountain Views
description:
Welcome to the STOKE Cabins next to Poley Mountain.

These stunning cabins set high on the mountainside offer awesome views of the Waterford Valley and have all of the luxuries to keep you cozy.

We've gone out of our way to make sure you can relax and enjoy your adventures knowing you have everything you need at basecamp.

Unwind after a day on the trails or experience the many adventures this place has to offer.
neighborhood_overview: Our cabins are build on a mountainside with incredible views of the Waterford Valley in the Caledonia Highlands. We are around the corner from Poley Mountain and at the center of the Watervord Valley. There is lots to do in the area. We have cut, built and marked two unique trails. The Flow Trail follows a quiet brook nestled in a valley while the Elevation Trail is a straight climb to the top of the ski resort. There is sightseeing all around and there are many awesome activities and day adventures to be had within a few minutes drive.
host_about: Stoke Resorts is not just about accommodations; it's about experiences. Our luxurious cabins come fully equipped with modern amenities, ensuring a comfortable stay. But beyond that, we aim to build an experience inspired by nature and community. From tips that take you to hidden gems to nearby spots to help you soak in the local culture, we've got something for everyone.

description: Enjoy panoramic ocean views from a contemporary waterfront home. Wake up with the sunrise over Passamaquoddy Bay (Bay of Fundy). neighborhood_overview:
Our neighbourhood is quiet, with mostly permanent residents on large lots around Passamaquoddy Bay. There is a public road that goes down to the beach next to the property.

St. Andrews-by-the-Sea is Canada's gem - a go-to for whale watching & other sea life, golfing, a farmer's market, museums, art, restaurants. An incredible amount of history and charm year round. We would love to make sure you have all the info you need to have the vacation experience that is right for you.
host_about:
I spend my time chasing around my two little girls with my husband, Justin. I grew up in Northern Ontario, surrounded by a New Brunswick marketing campaign carefully overseen by my Fredericton parents. Posters, art, music - even little figurines of Saint Andrews, where Justin and I are hosts. 

We spent every family vacation on the east coast & now I get to do the same with my daughters. In between, we hope you enjoy our home.

name: Campobello Island Cozy Cottage Retreats
description:
Vocational Summer Retreats & Cottage Living

Come Visit Une BelleVue Where Eagles Soar for:

â€¢ Personal Relaxation
â€¢ Weekend Getaways
â€¢ Intimate Getaways
â€¢ Romantic Getaways
â€¢ Pillow Talks
â€¢ Nature's Retreat
â€¢ Fresh Air Getaways

Our house, "Une BelleVue", is an 864 sq ft 2 bedroom cozy bungalow resting on an acre of spectacular views of the Atlantic Ocean, on the beautiful Island of Campobello, NB Canada. 15 minutes from Lubec, Maine.

Bookings Available For Quiet Time...
neighborhood_overview:
It's very peaceful here at "Une BelleVue", where the sunrise is a spectacular view from the house.

Most mornings you'll see the eagles and other birds flying over head calling to each other, enjoying the ocean breeze as they soar the skies. You will also see and hear our beautiful small squirrels scurrying around looking for food and woodpeckers pecking at the bark of the trees. Hope you get to see the "Pileated Woodpecker", they are big and beautiful.

If you bring your bikes there are lots of trails and parks to visit.

You can also drive around the Island, where you will have different views of nearby islands and see the ferry coming into Welshpool.

From the backyard or living room you will also see the Grand Manan Ferries in the distance as they sail by, and watch the fishing boats coming in or going out.

Please note...Book in advance for weekend stays as there are No Saturday Bookings
host_about: Just being me, loveable, and easy to talk to...

name: Beachfront Country Cottage Getaway
description: This unique beachfront property is a 1908 country church converted into a charming cottage.
neighborhood_overview:
This is a quiet rural area surrounded by the ocean, farms and forest. Nearby walking trails, several beaches, farmers markets, fish markets, a winery and local cafe, as well as nearby access to PEI and Nova Scotia's Sunrise Trail.

https://www.todaysparent.com/family/20-great-canadian-summer-getaways/
host_about:
Iâ€™m a Nova Scotian by birth, with proud Scottish heritage, but now call rural New Brunswick my home. I work as a Financial Planner and host Airbnb guests at my very unique beachfront converted church. 

My objective is for my guests to have a great experience in a sparkling clean, comfortable space, enjoying the beach and huge property and all that the area has to offer.  The area itself is very unique in that fishing and farming exist side by side.  As a result, my guests enjoy the best of country and beachside living.  We are also unique in that we immediately border both PEI and Nova Scotia, so this is an easy jump off point to visit all three provinces.

Our area is famous for the best lobster, oysters, clams and scallops anywhere on the planet. Here, you can take a short drive to the local wharf and buy lobster straight from the fishing boat, at a very reasonable price, and cook it fresh in sea water!

Weâ€™ve also got excellent local restaurants serving our areaâ€™s best local produce and seafood!

Acadian cultural experiences are nearby, along with the very popular destinations of Hopewell Rocks, Fundy National Park, Kougibouguac National Park, Shediac and Parlee Beach, Aboiteau Wharf and Beach and The Dunes at Bouctouche.  

There is no better place to experience so much, while offering the tranquility of the countryside and the beaches.
